<item>
            <title>[FELIX-1634] Maven Bundle Plugin disables transitive dependencies</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-1634</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;By its setup Maven Bundle Plugin disables transitive dependencies by it&apos;s setup of org.apache.maven.artifact.handler.ArtifactHandler in /META-INF/plexus/components.xml. The setting: &amp;lt;includesDependencies&amp;gt;true&amp;lt;/includesDependencies&amp;gt; means that an artifact of type &quot;bundle&quot; will include everything it needs in the jar and dependencies are not transitive. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This setting should be &quot;false&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that this is only observable only when you depend on a &quot;bundle&quot; and you have the &amp;lt;type&amp;gt;bundle&amp;lt;/type&amp;gt; set.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
